            "title": "Reviva Pharma Holdings announces $9 million public offering, selling 27,000,000 shares at $0.335/share with Series E and F warrants.",
            "id": "f7783e0a-5b77-4853-bbea-e39dd9aec6ca",
            "description": "On September 18, 2025, Reviva Pharmaceuticals Holdings, Inc. (NASDAQ: RVPH) disclosed the pricing details of their recent public offering. The offering involved the sale of 27,000,000 shares of common stock (or equivalents) alongside Series E warrants for 27,000,000 common stock shares and Series F warrants for 27,000,000 common stock shares. These were made available to existing and new institutional investors at a combined price of $0.335 per share and accompanying warrants. The total gross proceeds from this offering sum up to approximately $9 million, before factoring in placement agent fees and other expenses related to the offering. Reviva is a late-stage pharmaceutical company concentrating on developing treatments for unmet medical needs in central nervous system, inflammatory, and cardiometabolic diseases.",
